Robin Soderling Beats Ferrer in Straight Sets in Swedish Open Final

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-07-17T17:52:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-17/robin-soderling-beats-david-ferrer-in-straight-sets-in-swedish-open-final.html
Top-seed Robin Soderling beat  David Ferrer  in straight sets to win tennis’s Swedish Open in Bastad
after reaching the final of his home event for a third straight
year.  Soderling, 26, who beat his Spanish opponent 6-2, 6-2 in 67
minutes, also took the title in 2009 and was the runner-up last
year.  The Swede, ranked  No. 5 on the ATP World Tour , has won all
four of his finals this season and takes his career record
against world No. 6 Ferrer to 10 victories in 14 meetings.  Elsewhere, Maria Jose Martinez of  Spain  beat  Austria ’s
Patricia Mayr-Achleitner 6-0, 7-5 to take a WTA title in Bad
Gastein, Austria.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 James Cone  in  London  at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 